<h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">Environmental Justice Activists Are Leading a Green New Deal Revolution</h1>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<div class="row featured-media-block"><figure class="featured-media" itemprop="image" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject">
<noscript><img width="1200" height="800" src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-1200x800.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt='A woman wearing red protests while holding a sign that reads "OUR HEALTH OVER YOUR PROFITS"' itemprop="url" srcset="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-200x133.jpg 200w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-400x267.jpg 400w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-800x534.jpg 800w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-e1559319929206.jpg 2400w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px"></noscript><img width="1200" height="800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203%202'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt='A woman wearing red protests while holding a sign that reads "OUR HEALTH OVER YOUR PROFITS"' itemprop="url" data-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-srcset="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-200x133.jpg 200w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-400x267.jpg 400w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-800x534.jpg 800w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-e1559319929206.jpg 2400w" data-src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sharon_march-1200x800.jpg" loading="lazy">
<figcaption class="wp-caption-text" itemprop="caption">Sharon Lavigne, Rev. Gregory Manning and other environmental justice activists lead the March Against Death Alley, a five-day march through Louisiana’s petrochemical corridor demanding an end to pollution in historic Black communities.</figcaption><figcaption class="wp-caption-credit" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name">Laura Borealis</span></figcaption></figure></div>
